Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicConman
    Basic version of the conman without any level badges.
    BuyOrder
    BuyOrder is a type of order that gains hitcoins to the trader which created it when it reaches it target.
    BuyOrderFactory
    This class is responsible for the creation of the BuyOrders.
    ChaseClosest
    This state checks the nearest Orders and tries to move to the position of the closest one for some time.
    Common
    This singleton class holds the common variables which all classes may need and also holds all the existing entities in the program.
    Conman
    Entities that try to collect Orders before they reach their destinations.
    ConmanDecorator
    Parent class of Conman decorations.
    Display
    This class extends JPanes and is responsible for the drawing of all the Entity s to the window.
    Entity
    Base class for all animation entities.
    Expert
    Expert decoration for the Conman.
    GotoXY
    This state determines a random point in the area where conmans can travel and goes to this target point with a random speed.
    HitcoinRunner
    Hitcoin Runner
    Master
    Master decoration for the Conman.
    Novice
    Novice decoration for the Conman.
    Order
    Order entity, which is represented as a ball on the screen.
    OrderFactory
    A High level factory class to be used with BuyOrderFactory and SellOrderFactory
    PricePlot
    Price plot entity on top of the screen.
    Rest
    In this state the conman keeps its position of an amount of time.
    SellOrder
    SellOrder is a type of order that gains hitcoins to the trader which created it when it reaches it target.
    SellOrderFactory
    This class is responsible for the creation of the SellOrders.
    Shake
    In this state the conman 'shakes' randomly for an amount of time.
    State
    Base class for all the states.
    Ticker
    The ticker at the bottom of the screen, it shows 100 companies from BIST in a random order each time the program is started.
    Trader
    Trader entities at the near the bottom of the screen.
    Vec2
    A 2d vector class to easily handle positions of the objects.
